  "title": "Tapping for the \"I never sleep\" story",
  "subtitle": "A five-minute script for releasing a sleep identity that has become self-reinforcing.",
  "excerpt": "A five-minute tapping practice from Day 11 of the SLEEP program. The script targets the identity-level pattern behind chronic sleeplessness: the label \"I'm a bad sleeper\" repeated so often it has become instruction.",
  "type": "PRACTICE",
  "sourceNotes": "Adapted from Day 11 of SLEEP: A 30-Day Tapping Intensive to Fall Asleep Faster and Wake Energised (Rebecca J Page, 2025, ISBN 9798269649795), \"Heal the 'I Can't Sleep' Story.\" Tapping framework: Gary Craig's Emotional Freedom Technique (EFT), in use since the mid-1990s, building on Roger Callahan's Thought Field Therapy.",
